Former Nigeria Super Eagles midfielder Justice Christopher is dead. Andrew Randa, the media officer of Nigeria Men’s U20 National Team, announced Christopher’s death in a tweet on Wednesday. Randa disclosed that Christopher died in the early hours of Wednesday morning at a hotel in Jos, Plateau State in Nigeria. Christopher made 11 appearances for the Super Eagles and was part of Nigeria’s squad to the 2002 FIFA World Cup in Korea/Japan. Details later. 